text: The 2003–04 Israeli Noar Leumit League was the 10th season since its introduction in 1994 as the top-tier football in Israel for teenagers between the ages 18–20. Maccabi Haifa won the title, whilst Hapoel Be'er Sheva and Gadna Yehuda were relegated. ==Final table== ==External links== *Noar Premier League 03-04 One.co.il Category:Israeli Noar Premier League seasons Youth
